{
  "texts": [
    "For a model to fully recover all the properties of the system, it must be as complex as the actual system.",
    "Perfect in theory, but too complicated to handle, it becomes impractical.",
    "Therefore, it is necessary to \"choose something to do and ignore others\" and simplify the model to the point where it can be handled.",
    "When it comes to mechanistic research, further simplification is required to the extent that the mechanism can be analyzed clearly, which is exactly what some mechanism studies do at the beginning.",
    "Research based on simple models provides cognitive basis and technical basis for subsequent research on more complex or realistic situations."
  ]
}